<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-219-004  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 219 004.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Vision Graphics andamp; Image Processing  May 1989 v46 n2p162(13).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Contrast enhancement technique based on local detection of edges.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Beghdadi, Azeddine; Le Negrate, Alain.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Attempts have been made to optimize the visual quality of an imagefor human or machine vision through gray-scale or histogrammodifications, which try to enhance the contrast of the inputimage without measuring the contrast itself.andP;  Only the localcontrast associated to each pixel in a specific neighborhood isconsidered here.andP;  Computing the differences between the signal ineach picture element and those in adjacent pixels and amplifyingthe differences enhances local contrast.andP;  Another definition isproposed of the contrast, associated to a pixel in a specificneighborhood, based on some physical criteria in an attempt toimprove Gordon's algorithm for use in problematic images.andO;Considering the theory of edge detection operators and visualperception criteria allows this technique to be realized.andP;  Thedigital processing technique enhances image contrast withoutsignificantly increasing noise.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Edge DetectionImage ProcessingTheoretical ResearchMathematics of ComputingNew TechniqueAlgorithm AnalysisComputer VisionEnhancementsContrast.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Window configuration of Gordon's contrast definition. (chart)Contrast enhancement of a simulated image. (chart)Classical contrast enhancement of the original image. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>